All 17 tests passing. Here's a summary of the changes:

**`Conversations.tsx`** — 3-line fix:
```typescript
const canSeeInternalNotes = role === 'vendor' || role === 'admin';
const messages = (activeConv?.messages ?? []).filter(
  (m) => !m.isInternal || canSeeInternalNotes,
);
```
Internal messages are stripped client-side before `messages.map(...)` runs, so neither the message content nor the `🔒 Internal Note` label ever reaches the DOM for unauthorized roles.

**`Conversations.internalNotes.test.tsx`** — 7 new tests covering:
- `vendor` and `admin` **can** see internal note content and the lock label
- `shopper`, `ops_reviewer`, and `finance_admin` **cannot** see internal note content
- `shopper` does not see the `🔒 Internal Note` label (regression guard)

